WEBVTT

00:36.133 --> 00:39.133
Rick: Babe?

00:39.167 --> 00:41.433
I got you a little surprise.

00:41.467 --> 00:44.100
I think you're gonna like it.

00:44.567 --> 00:46.800
I saw Luke playing ball
down the street,

00:46.833 --> 00:51.133
so I know that we are
all alone right now.

00:51.167 --> 00:53.400
Just the two of us, baby.

00:53.433 --> 00:57.000
Ooh, man, that turkey
smells fantastic.

00:58.700 --> 01:01.500
[Jenna gasping]

01:01.533 --> 01:03.100
Rick: Hey.

01:03.133 --> 01:05.100
Sam Jenkins:
Well, isn't that sweet?

01:05.133 --> 01:07.100
Go ahead and pull it!

01:07.133 --> 01:09.333
[coughing]

01:09.367 --> 01:11.100
Rick: Baby, go
out back right now.

01:11.133 --> 01:13.467
Sam: Honey,
you just stay right there.

01:16.200 --> 01:18.400
Sit down!

01:19.833 --> 01:21.567
Rick: She got nothing
to do with this, Jenkins.

01:21.600 --> 01:23.733
Sam: She's got
everything to do with this.

01:23.767 --> 01:30.500
My wife, my kids, my life,
you took 'em all from me!

01:30.533 --> 01:32.067
Rick: What do you want?

01:32.100 --> 01:34.467
Sam: What do I want?

01:34.500 --> 01:36.233
How about a cure for cancer?

01:36.267 --> 01:38.733
[coughing]

01:41.400 --> 01:43.467
I'm dying, detective.

01:43.500 --> 01:45.133
I'm gonna die cold
and alone

01:45.167 --> 01:48.333
and I want you to know
what that feels like.

01:49.533 --> 01:51.233
What are you, a ninja?

01:51.267 --> 01:54.100
Keep moving towards me,
detective, I'm begging you.

01:54.133 --> 01:56.400
Rick: Turn around
right now and leave.

01:56.433 --> 01:57.767
No harm, no foul.

01:57.800 --> 02:01.233
Sam: Oh, really?
No harm, no foul?

02:01.267 --> 02:03.800
[coughing]

02:03.833 --> 02:05.767
How about this for harm and--

02:05.800 --> 02:09.133
[timer dings]

02:09.167 --> 02:11.167
[gunshot fires]

02:13.467 --> 02:23.500
[music]

02:23.500 --> 02:28.467
[music]

02:28.567 --> 02:38.567
[music]

02:38.667 --> 02:41.333
* There's something
about this place *

02:41.367 --> 02:44.400
* Like a warm embrace

02:44.433 --> 02:48.533
* I found the road
that leads me home *

02:50.567 --> 02:56.567
* I need some grace
to find the way *

02:56.600 --> 03:00.100
* to bear my heart

03:02.367 --> 03:06.367
* Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh

03:06.400 --> 03:12.533
* I'm finding you're
what I want *

03:13.300 --> 03:16.533
* but you're gone

03:18.500 --> 03:24.633
* You got nowhere to go
and I don't belong *

03:24.667 --> 03:30.733
* Without you,
I can't stay here *

03:30.767 --> 03:37.100
* But I need your grace
to help me find the way *

03:37.133 --> 03:40.633
* and heal my heart

03:42.433 --> 03:46.567
* Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh

03:46.600 --> 03:55.367
* I'm finding you're
what I want *

03:57.100 --> 04:02.200
* Lost
So lost *

04:02.233 --> 04:07.200
* All too familiar,
this road ahead *

04:09.067 --> 04:14.467
* Lost
So lost *

04:14.500 --> 04:21.033
* Inside the memories,
I reach the end *

04:23.567 --> 04:25.667
* Is this the end? *

04:27.167 --> 04:29.167
[knocking]

04:46.567 --> 04:48.067
[knocking]

04:48.100 --> 04:50.367
Rick: Yeah, coming.

04:57.800 --> 05:00.000
Cap'n.

05:12.667 --> 05:14.733
Captain Moss Williams:
Oh, I'm good.

05:17.267 --> 05:19.533
I called your cell phone.

05:19.567 --> 05:22.100
It says it's disconnected.

05:22.133 --> 05:24.467
Rick: Right.

05:26.133 --> 05:29.333
Moss: How you
holdin' up, partner?

05:29.367 --> 05:31.767
Rick: Living the dream.

05:33.133 --> 05:39.100
Moss: Any Thanksgiving plans?

05:39.133 --> 05:41.467
Rick: You're looking at it.

05:43.533 --> 05:46.233
Moss: How's Luke doing?

05:46.667 --> 05:49.100
Rick: Moss, I appreciate
you stopping by.

05:49.133 --> 05:51.400
I'm good.

05:52.567 --> 05:55.367
Moss: Why don't you come by
and check out the game later?

05:55.400 --> 05:57.533
Got a new 70-inch screen TV.

05:57.567 --> 05:59.633
It's gonna be great.

05:59.667 --> 06:03.433
And you know Irene
cooks up a mean turkey.

06:04.100 --> 06:06.300
Rick: Yeah, maybe.

06:07.633 --> 06:11.600
Moss: Hard to believe,
5 years ago already.

06:16.200 --> 06:18.633
[gunshots firing]

06:21.267 --> 06:23.467
Moss: Game starts at 1.

06:23.500 --> 06:25.267
Come on by, man.

06:25.300 --> 06:27.567
Rick: Happy Thanksgiving,
Captain.

