08:00.833 --> 08:07.500
[music]

08:07.600 --> 08:08.300
[phone beeps]

08:08.333 --> 08:10.200
[female on voicemail]
Ricky?

08:10.233 --> 08:11.800
Sweetheart?

08:11.833 --> 08:13.733
Are you there?

08:13.767 --> 08:16.233
It's just me again.

08:16.267 --> 08:19.633
I just really wish
you'd pick up.

08:20.367 --> 08:24.433
Well, anyway, the turkey's
gonna be ready around 4,

08:24.467 --> 08:27.400
and we'd really love to see you.

08:27.433 --> 08:30.467
I know a certain someone
who is missing you a lot.

08:30.500 --> 08:31.700
Luke: Grandma's here!

08:31.733 --> 08:33.133
We can eat!
We can eat!

08:33.167 --> 08:34.467
[female on voicemail]
So, please,

08:34.500 --> 08:36.767
just try to make it,
okay?

08:36.800 --> 08:38.400
Jenna: My first turkey.

08:38.433 --> 08:40.433
Not bad, huh?

08:42.567 --> 08:44.200
[female on voicemail]
Ricky?

08:44.233 --> 08:46.333
Honey?

08:46.367 --> 08:49.333
Okay, bye-bye.

09:00.800 --> 09:03.233
Rick: Ain't nothing
in those cans.

09:04.100 --> 09:07.200
Jeremiah: One man's trash
is another man's treasure.

09:12.167 --> 09:13.200
Rick: Here.

09:13.233 --> 09:15.100
Jeremiah: Oh, no.
I'm good.

09:15.133 --> 09:17.500
Rick: Well, I have to leave,
so can you move?

09:17.533 --> 09:19.733
Jeremiah: Important
places to go, I bet.

09:20.400 --> 09:21.500
Rick: What?

09:21.533 --> 09:23.633
Jeremiah: Well, I used to be
in a hurry all the time,

09:23.667 --> 09:27.100
always on the go,
never stopping to enjoy

09:27.133 --> 09:30.567
everything the good Lord
laid right under our noses.

09:30.600 --> 09:33.300
Rick: How's that
working out for you?

09:34.500 --> 09:36.367
Jeremiah: Family plans?

09:36.400 --> 09:37.767
Rick: I really can't do this.

09:37.800 --> 09:39.367
Not today.

09:39.400 --> 09:41.700
Jeremiah: It's
Thanksgiving Day.

09:42.433 --> 09:46.400
A young man like you
oughta be with family.

09:46.433 --> 09:49.300
Looks like you got a lot
to be thankful for.

09:51.200 --> 09:54.000
Rick: Looks like you got
a lot to be thankful for.

10:10.500 --> 10:15.300
Jeremiah: It's a beautiful day,
I'm alive, and God is good.

10:15.333 --> 10:16.633
Rick: Is he?

10:16.667 --> 10:18.633
Jeremiah: Sure.

10:18.667 --> 10:21.033
Oh, I know what you're thinking.

10:21.067 --> 10:25.433
Well, you're right.
You're right.

10:27.167 --> 10:32.467
I wasted a lot of the years
God gave me.

10:32.500 --> 10:34.133
But you?

10:34.167 --> 10:36.533
You got your whole life
in front of you.

10:36.567 --> 10:38.433
Rick: Enough of the words
of wisdom.

10:38.467 --> 10:41.667
Here, go grab a bite
or a new jacket.

10:41.700 --> 10:45.467
Jeremiah: I've got everything
I need right inside of me.

10:45.500 --> 10:47.567
Rick: Suit yourself.

10:47.600 --> 10:49.367
Jeremiah: Happy Thanksgiving,
friend.

10:49.400 --> 10:51.633
Rick: Same to you.

10:51.667 --> 10:56.267
Jeremiah: You know, God
never lets us down, ever.

10:56.300 --> 10:58.467
Rick: And never gives us
more than we can handle, right?

10:58.500 --> 11:01.100
Jeremiah: That's right.

11:02.333 --> 11:05.100
Rick: What happens if it
is more than we can handle?

11:05.133 --> 11:07.467
Then what?

11:15.333 --> 11:25.367
[music]

11:25.367 --> 11:30.333
[music]

11:30.433 --> 11:44.667
[music]

11:44.767 --> 11:47.500
Rick: List what
you're thankful for.

11:47.533 --> 11:50.233
That'd be a short list.

11:59.500 --> 12:01.767
[Grace sighing]

12:10.100 --> 12:11.733
Wait!

12:12.367 --> 12:15.000
Rick: Sorry lady.
Not today.

