14:48.567 --> 14:54.233
[music]

14:54.333 --> 14:55.767
Grace: Hi!

14:55.800 --> 14:58.367
Excuse me!

14:59.333 --> 15:02.167
Oh my god.
I'm so sorry.

15:02.200 --> 15:04.300
I'm just a mess.

15:04.333 --> 15:06.500
It's Thanksgiving,
I don't have a cell phone.

15:06.533 --> 15:09.367
I could use a little help,
please.

15:09.400 --> 15:10.667
Rick: Sorry, lady.

15:10.700 --> 15:12.500
You picked the wrong guy
on the wrong day.

15:12.533 --> 15:14.100
Grace: That can't be true.

15:14.133 --> 15:15.633
Nothing happens on accident.

15:15.667 --> 15:17.667
Everything happens for a reason.

15:17.700 --> 15:19.333
Rick: Would you
just spit it out?

15:19.367 --> 15:21.133
Tell me what you want.

15:21.167 --> 15:22.433
Grace: Oh, right.

15:22.467 --> 15:25.267
Can I please
borrow your phone?

15:25.300 --> 15:28.167
Rick: Sorry, I don't have
a cell phone.

15:28.200 --> 15:30.033
Grace: Really?

15:30.067 --> 15:32.133
Who doesn't have
a cell phone these days?

15:32.167 --> 15:34.400
Rick: Apparently
neither of us.

15:34.433 --> 15:37.300
Grace: Right.
Ugh.

15:37.333 --> 15:38.600
Rick: Even if you had
a cell phone,

15:38.633 --> 15:40.400
you're not gonna get
a cab to come out here

15:40.433 --> 15:42.667
in the middle of nowhere
and pick you up on Thanksgiving.

15:42.700 --> 15:44.167
Grace: So, there's
no chance you're

15:44.200 --> 15:48.367
gonna be driving into town
anytime soon?

15:49.233 --> 15:51.500
Rick: I'm sure if you just
walk back out to the highway,

15:51.533 --> 15:53.200
someone'll come along
and pick you up,

15:53.233 --> 15:54.800
take you to town.

15:54.833 --> 15:58.400
Grace: I guess
that's a no, isn't it?

15:59.633 --> 16:03.433
Okay, I'm so sorry
for disturbing you.

16:03.467 --> 16:07.433
You have a nice Thanksgiving,
and God bless.

16:07.467 --> 16:17.467
[music]

16:17.567 --> 16:27.467
[music]

16:27.567 --> 16:37.600
[music]

16:37.600 --> 16:42.467
[music]

17:00.200 --> 17:02.200
Rick: I guess
it's your lucky day.

17:02.233 --> 17:04.433
Grace: Really?

17:04.467 --> 17:06.233
Rick: You better hurry up
before I change my mind.

17:06.267 --> 17:07.767
Grace: Oh god, thank you!

17:07.800 --> 17:10.300
Thank you so much.

17:11.567 --> 17:13.300
Rick: Here, I'll help you
with your--

17:13.333 --> 17:15.400
Grace: It's okay.
Thank you, thank you.

17:17.300 --> 17:20.500
Rick: You can sit
in the--

17:20.533 --> 17:23.367
Okay.

17:23.400 --> 17:33.433
[music]

17:33.433 --> 17:38.400
[music]

17:38.500 --> 17:47.200
[music]

17:47.300 --> 17:48.633
Rick: Yeah,
where are we headed?

17:48.667 --> 17:50.333
Grace: Home, please.

17:50.367 --> 17:53.067
I'm gonna be with
my family today.

17:53.100 --> 17:55.067
Rick: And home is?

17:55.100 --> 17:56.367
Grace: Silly me.

17:56.400 --> 17:58.067
Like you would know
where I live, right?

17:58.100 --> 18:00.167
You know, the Lord is
gonna bless you for this.

18:00.200 --> 18:02.200
I promise.

18:02.233 --> 18:04.167
Rick: Of course he is.

18:04.200 --> 18:06.200
Grace: Here it is.

18:13.333 --> 18:16.200
To serve and protect.

18:16.767 --> 18:21.300
Wow, God knew what he was
doing when he sent you my way.

18:21.333 --> 18:23.667
Rick: Huh?

18:24.433 --> 18:26.400
Where'd you--

18:27.267 --> 18:28.500
Thanks.

18:28.533 --> 18:30.433
Grace: So, you're a cop?

18:30.467 --> 18:32.033
Rick: Was.

18:32.067 --> 18:34.600
Grace: You know, I never
got your name.

18:34.633 --> 18:37.767
Rick: Rick.

18:37.800 --> 18:39.400
Grace: Nice to meet you,
Rick.

18:39.433 --> 18:43.200
I'm Graciela.

18:43.233 --> 18:45.533
Rick: You're what?

18:45.567 --> 18:48.133
Grace: I'm Grace.

18:49.267 --> 18:51.533
Rick: Perfect.

18:54.833 --> 18:56.433
Rick, you're pathetic.

18:56.467 --> 18:57.667
Grace: What was that?

18:57.700 --> 18:59.767
Rick: Nothing, ma'am.

19:06.200 --> 19:08.567
Rick: So, does this say--

19:09.133 --> 19:11.233
This is clear on
the other side of town.

19:11.267 --> 19:12.500
Grace: I know.

19:12.533 --> 19:14.100
I don't know what
I was thinking,

19:14.133 --> 19:16.733
trying to go all
the way on foot.

19:16.767 --> 19:19.167
I would've never made it.

19:19.200 --> 19:21.567
You're a life saver.

19:26.233 --> 19:29.200
It's funny how different
things look sometimes.

19:29.233 --> 19:32.433
You ever notice that?

19:32.467 --> 19:35.767
Gosh, the streets are so empty.

19:36.533 --> 19:40.467
Guess everyone's enjoying it
with their families today.

19:40.500 --> 19:44.800
I can almost smell all
the turkeys in the oven.

19:44.833 --> 19:55.067
[music]

19:55.067 --> 20:00.033
[music]

20:00.133 --> 20:14.267
[music]

20:14.367 --> 20:16.400
Grace: That was
so rude of me.

20:16.433 --> 20:18.233
Rick: What's that?

20:18.267 --> 20:20.133
Grace: Falling asleep
like that.

20:20.167 --> 20:23.333
I've just been
so worn down lately.

20:23.367 --> 20:25.667
Rick: No worries.

20:25.700 --> 20:27.533
Grace: I can't wait
to be with my family.

20:27.567 --> 20:30.267
I'm sure you're gonna
be with your family too.

20:31.167 --> 20:33.633
But I'm really thankful
and grateful that I'm riding

20:33.667 --> 20:36.400
in this car with you
and that I'm not dragging

20:36.433 --> 20:38.100
that old suitcase around.

20:38.133 --> 20:40.367
I would've never made it.

20:41.833 --> 20:44.333
Are you a man of faith?

20:45.067 --> 20:47.233
Rick: What's that, ma'am?

20:47.267 --> 20:51.100
Grace: You know, faith, God?

20:52.267 --> 20:54.467
Rick: I don't really
think about it much, ma'am.

20:54.500 --> 20:57.500
Grace: Oh, that's too bad.

20:58.167 --> 20:59.733
I don't know how anyone
can get through it all

20:59.767 --> 21:01.533
without a little faith.

21:01.567 --> 21:04.567
I have this feeling like you
have to hang onto that hope

21:04.600 --> 21:07.800
that there's something
bigger than we are,

21:07.833 --> 21:10.233
that there's a purpose
to it all.

21:10.667 --> 21:13.233
We're gonna have
to work on that, Mister.

21:13.267 --> 21:14.700
Rick: Sorry, ma'am?

21:14.733 --> 21:18.133
Grace: Your faith, or lack
of faith I suppose.

21:18.167 --> 21:21.133
And please call me Grace.

21:21.167 --> 21:23.567
Rick: Whatever you say,
Grace.

21:23.600 --> 21:25.367
Grace: Is there a turkey
waiting for you at home?

21:25.400 --> 21:27.300
Rick: I'm finding it hard
to focus on the road, Grace,

21:27.333 --> 21:28.733
with all the questions.

21:28.767 --> 21:31.267
Grace: Right.
I'm so sorry.

21:31.300 --> 21:33.100
You wouldn't believe this,
but I'm like the last person

21:33.133 --> 21:35.167
you would ever accuse
of being a motor mouth,

21:35.200 --> 21:38.100
let alone being nosey.

21:38.133 --> 21:40.300
Just for some reason,
I just can't shut up.

21:41.333 --> 21:43.333
Sorry.

21:43.733 --> 21:46.467
Rick: Let's just
get you home.

21:46.500 --> 21:50.700
Grace: Actually, if you make
a right up here.

21:50.733 --> 21:53.267
Rick: Right here?

21:56.200 --> 21:57.600
Grace: Yes, stop.
Stop, stop, stop.

21:57.633 --> 22:00.267
Rick: Stop?
Grace?

22:06.500 --> 22:09.033
Where's she going?

22:09.067 --> 22:10.700
Hey!

22:10.733 --> 22:13.133
Grace?

22:14.067 --> 22:16.033
What the?

22:16.067 --> 22:18.133
Grace?

22:19.833 --> 22:22.167
Grace!
Hey!

22:22.200 --> 22:23.600
Wait up, will you?

22:23.633 --> 22:25.633
Grace!

22:26.600 --> 22:28.567
What are you?
Grace!

22:28.600 --> 22:30.100
No, no, no.

22:30.133 --> 22:31.333
Hey, don't go--

22:31.367 --> 22:33.400
Don't go in there.

22:33.433 --> 22:35.800
Hey!

22:35.833 --> 22:37.600
Grace!

22:37.633 --> 22:40.167
What are you--

22:42.233 --> 22:44.433
Grace?

22:45.333 --> 22:47.733
Grace?
Come here.

22:49.200 --> 22:51.267
What are you doing here?

22:51.767 --> 22:53.600
Hey.

22:53.633 --> 22:54.767
Grace: Come on!

22:54.800 --> 22:56.200
Come on!

22:56.233 --> 22:58.267
Rick: Grace, please.

22:59.600 --> 23:02.600
Grace!
Grace!

23:02.633 --> 23:04.300
Hey!

23:04.333 --> 23:05.700
We shouldn't be in here.

23:05.733 --> 23:06.667
Grace: Oh, come on.

23:06.700 --> 23:08.300
You never snuck into
a high school before?

23:08.333 --> 23:10.567
Rick: No, I was too busy
sneaking out of school.

23:10.600 --> 23:14.600
Grace: I have
so many memories.

23:14.633 --> 23:16.433
I used to lay up there
in those bleachers,

23:16.467 --> 23:21.433
sun shining,
radio blasting.

23:21.467 --> 23:23.133
Rick: You went
to school here?

23:23.167 --> 23:24.367
Grace: You?

23:24.400 --> 23:25.800
Rick: Regional.

23:25.833 --> 23:27.600
We used to stomp
you guys in football.

23:27.633 --> 23:29.133
Grace: Oh yeah?

23:29.167 --> 23:30.767
We used to stomp you
right back in this pool.

23:30.800 --> 23:32.333
Rick: Yeah, that's
not really the same thing.

23:32.367 --> 23:33.767
Grace: Really?

23:33.800 --> 23:34.633
Rick: No.

23:34.667 --> 23:36.433
Grace: Oh, you
ready to back that up?

23:36.467 --> 23:38.433
Rick: No, I'm not a big
fan of the pool.

23:38.467 --> 23:39.633
Grace: Oh, someone's
being a chicken.

23:39.667 --> 23:40.533
Bawk, bawk, bawk, bawk, bawk!

23:40.567 --> 23:42.300
Rick: No, someone wants
to get out of here

23:42.333 --> 23:44.600
before we get caught.

23:49.433 --> 23:52.633
Grace: I remember the final
meet like it was yesterday.

23:52.667 --> 23:57.567
Senior year, this place
was packed.

23:57.600 --> 24:00.100
We'd run most of our races.

24:00.133 --> 24:01.700
Well, my team had.

24:01.733 --> 24:05.467
I wasn't really that good,
but I didn't care.

24:05.500 --> 24:08.333
I was happy to cheer my team on.

24:08.367 --> 24:10.300
Rick: Grace?

24:10.333 --> 24:14.367
Grace: For some reason,
I don't know why,

24:14.400 --> 24:19.467
I looked up and there he was.

24:20.133 --> 24:25.200
He was sitting right here
next to my mom.

24:25.233 --> 24:29.667
My dad had actually
made it to a meet.

24:29.700 --> 24:31.300
You don't understand.

24:31.333 --> 24:35.500
In 4 years, my dad had
never made it to a meet.

24:35.533 --> 24:40.600
He was always traveling,
always too busy.

24:40.633 --> 24:45.133
And he was there, clapping
and cheering me on

24:45.167 --> 24:48.533
like it was the Olympics
or something.

24:48.567 --> 24:50.233
At first, I didn't
know what to do.

24:50.267 --> 24:51.600
I was a little embarrassed.

24:51.633 --> 24:53.367
I'm sitting on the bench,
passing out towels,

24:53.400 --> 24:55.267
and he didn't care.

24:55.300 --> 24:58.667
He was so proud of me.

25:00.167 --> 25:03.133
You wouldn't believe
what happened next.

25:03.733 --> 25:05.367
Rick: What?

25:05.400 --> 25:06.767
Grace: The whole team's
calling my name.

25:06.800 --> 25:08.333
"Grace! Grace! Grace!"

25:08.367 --> 25:11.467
And I'm, like, staring
at my dad, oblivious.

25:11.500 --> 25:14.067
Finally, one of the girls
grabs me and she pulls me.

25:14.100 --> 25:16.333
And she points at the coach,
and the coach is frantic,

25:16.367 --> 25:18.033
calling me over.

25:18.067 --> 25:20.767
And I'm like, "What
did I do wrong now?"

25:20.800 --> 25:23.267
It was the final relay
of the day.

25:23.300 --> 25:27.300
One of the girls got hurt
or something.

25:27.333 --> 25:31.033
And for some reason,
the coach was calling my name.

25:31.067 --> 25:33.433
Rick: What'd you do?

25:33.467 --> 25:35.433
Grace: I swam.

25:35.467 --> 25:40.567
I swam like I had
never swam before.

25:43.667 --> 25:45.367
And we won!

25:45.400 --> 25:47.300
We actually won.

25:47.333 --> 25:50.000
It was awesome.

25:51.200 --> 25:52.800
And that race
qualified us to regionals,

25:52.833 --> 25:57.267
and the rest,
like they say, is history.

25:58.100 --> 26:01.267
Well, at least around
these parts, it's a big deal.

26:01.300 --> 26:03.600
Rick: Yeah.

26:04.600 --> 26:10.133
Grace: There was my daddy,
just cheering me on.

26:21.167 --> 26:27.433
What I didn't know
was that....

26:27.467 --> 26:31.500
he had already packed
all his things in his car.

26:38.567 --> 26:41.733
That was the last day
I saw him.

26:44.667 --> 26:46.767
Rick: That's rough.

26:46.800 --> 26:49.400
Grace: Yeah.

26:50.067 --> 26:51.633
You just don't know how much
you need your father

26:51.667 --> 26:54.467
until he's gone.

26:57.833 --> 26:59.467
I'm sorry.

26:59.500 --> 27:02.267
I don't even know why
I'm sharing this with you.

27:06.200 --> 27:08.200
Rick: Come on.

27:10.267 --> 27:11.667
Let's get you home.

27:11.700 --> 27:14.367
Grace: Yeah.

27:28.267 --> 27:29.367
Rick: Here.

27:29.400 --> 27:30.700
Grace: Thank you.

27:30.733 --> 27:31.800
Rick: Oh, here, let me.

27:31.833 --> 27:33.133
Grace: I got it.

27:33.167 --> 27:34.200
Rick: No, no, it's okay.

27:34.233 --> 27:35.400
Grace: I got it.

27:35.433 --> 27:36.400
Rick: No, it's fine.

27:36.433 --> 27:37.267
I just--

27:37.300 --> 27:38.767
Grace: I promise
it's in good hands.

27:38.800 --> 27:41.667
Rick: Okay, all right?

27:41.700 --> 27:43.300
Grace: Whoa, this is heavy.

27:43.333 --> 27:45.533
What do you have
in here, a toaster?

27:46.467 --> 27:48.633
Rick: No, no, no!

27:51.333 --> 27:52.600
Grace: Maybe I should go.

27:52.633 --> 27:54.200
Rick: I'm sorry.

27:54.233 --> 27:55.367
I didn't mean to do that.

27:55.400 --> 27:56.667
Grace: Look, I didn't mean
to upset you.

27:56.700 --> 27:58.767
Rick: No, it's just this--

27:58.800 --> 28:02.067
I just have some personal things
in here, that's all.

28:03.633 --> 28:06.333
Let me just take you home.

28:10.267 --> 28:12.400
Here.

28:13.667 --> 28:15.767
Will you keep that safe for me?

28:16.733 --> 28:18.733
Grace: Sure.

28:22.300 --> 28:32.333
[music]

28:32.333 --> 28:37.300
[music]

28:37.400 --> 28:47.433
[music]

28:47.433 --> 28:52.300
[music]

28:52.400 --> 29:02.433
[music]

29:02.433 --> 29:07.300
[music]

29:08.200 --> 29:09.567
Rick: Another surprise ahead?

29:09.600 --> 29:10.800
Grace: You never know.

29:10.833 --> 29:14.300
Rick: Just skip the breaking
and entering next time, okay?

29:14.333 --> 29:15.567
Grace: What breaking?

29:15.600 --> 29:17.700
I just jiggled the door
and it opened.

29:18.633 --> 29:21.500
Aye-aye, officer.

29:23.233 --> 29:24.600
Ah!

29:24.633 --> 29:26.600
So you can smile.

29:26.633 --> 29:28.533
I knew it!

29:28.567 --> 29:31.267
Rick: I smile.

29:31.833 --> 29:33.333
Grace: Wow.

29:33.367 --> 29:35.100
That was two in a row.

29:35.133 --> 29:37.500
You should smile more often.

29:37.533 --> 29:40.067
It looks good on you.

29:40.600 --> 29:43.200
You know, people would barely
notice how bad you dress

29:43.233 --> 29:45.100
if you smiled a little more.

29:45.133 --> 29:46.767
Rick: Hey!

29:46.800 --> 29:48.567
Grace: You know what
they say about a smile, right?

29:48.600 --> 29:49.767
Rick: What's that?

29:49.800 --> 29:51.333
Grace: A smile is like
tight underwear.

29:51.367 --> 29:53.233
It makes your cheeks go up.

29:53.267 --> 29:55.767
[laughing]

29:56.400 --> 29:58.633
Rick: That was really bad.

29:58.667 --> 30:00.333
[Grace laughing]

30:00.367 --> 30:02.367
Rick: That was so bad.

30:06.800 --> 30:08.233
[Grace screaming]
A dios mio!

30:08.267 --> 30:10.367
Watch out!

30:10.800 --> 30:12.667
Rick: Are you okay?

30:12.700 --> 30:14.767
Grace: You almost
killed a man.

30:15.433 --> 30:17.433
Rick: I know that guy.

30:18.067 --> 30:20.167
Hey!

30:20.200 --> 30:22.167
Are you okay, bud?

30:23.500 --> 30:25.133
Are you okay?

30:25.167 --> 30:27.667
Jeremiah: I've got a band
of angels watching over me.

30:27.700 --> 30:28.767
I'm all good.

30:28.800 --> 30:30.700
Rick: What are you doing
in the middle of the road?

30:30.733 --> 30:32.300
I mean, I could--

30:32.333 --> 30:33.767
Two seconds later.

30:33.800 --> 30:35.800
Jeremiah: We're all where
we're supposed to be

30:35.833 --> 30:38.633
at any given time.

30:38.667 --> 30:40.767
Rick: I can't say
the same for your cart.

30:42.567 --> 30:46.367
[Jeremiah laughing]

30:48.633 --> 30:50.500
Don't that feel good?

30:50.533 --> 30:53.200
Rick: What's that?

30:53.233 --> 30:54.567
Jeremiah: What's
the last time you had

30:54.600 --> 30:56.767
a good laugh like that, Rick?

30:56.800 --> 30:58.767
Rick: I couldn't even
tell you.

30:58.800 --> 31:00.700
How'd you know my name?

31:00.733 --> 31:02.567
Jeremiah: Oh, I know
who you are.

31:02.600 --> 31:05.333
Your wife, Jenna,
was a shining light

31:05.367 --> 31:08.133
to all of us at the shelter.

31:08.167 --> 31:10.433
Rick: Oh yeah.

31:10.467 --> 31:12.600
Yeah, she used to love
working down there.

31:12.633 --> 31:15.400
Jeremiah: We all miss her.

31:16.700 --> 31:18.600
Rick: Yeah.

31:18.633 --> 31:21.000
Jeremiah: I'm Jeremiah.

31:21.533 --> 31:22.767
Rick: Pleasure.

31:22.800 --> 31:25.433
Rick.

31:25.467 --> 31:27.767
Of course, you knew that.

31:28.433 --> 31:31.233
Grace: Everyone okay?

31:32.633 --> 31:35.367
Jeremiah: And who
is the pretty lady?

31:35.400 --> 31:39.300
Grace: Hi, I'm Grace.

31:39.333 --> 31:41.033
Jeremiah: Grace?

31:41.067 --> 31:42.267
A perfect name.

31:42.300 --> 31:43.700
Jeremiah.

31:43.733 --> 31:47.200
Grace: Jeremiah,
lifted up by God.

31:47.233 --> 31:48.600
Jeremiah: That's right.

31:48.633 --> 31:50.433
Smart lady.

31:50.467 --> 31:52.667
You know, I think the Lord
knew just what he was doing

31:52.700 --> 31:55.200
when he put this cart
in your path.

31:55.233 --> 31:58.100
I have something for you.

31:59.100 --> 32:01.333
I was gonna give it
to you this morning,

32:01.367 --> 32:06.133
but you were in such
a hurry that I didn't.

32:06.167 --> 32:11.200
And then, I--well, this belongs
to your son, Luke.

32:14.300 --> 32:16.167
Rick: Where'd you get this?

32:16.200 --> 32:18.600
Jeremiah: Jenna used to bring
Luke by the shelter

32:18.633 --> 32:22.700
from time to time, and I would
play catch with him out back.

32:22.733 --> 32:27.100
Well, one day he left it there,
and when we didn't hear--

32:27.133 --> 32:30.700
Anyway, I thought I would
keep it secure.

32:33.433 --> 32:35.633
Rick: Thank you.

32:35.667 --> 32:39.333
Jeremiah: Now you can give
it to him yourself,

32:39.367 --> 32:44.533
although I suppose you bought
him a new one a long time ago.

32:44.567 --> 32:59.267
[music]

32:59.300 --> 33:01.767
Grace: You okay?

33:01.800 --> 33:06.567
Rick: I never liked her
working down at that shelter,

33:06.600 --> 33:09.200
all the riffraff.

33:10.133 --> 33:13.167
Maybe I was wrong.

33:13.800 --> 33:17.133
She always saw
the good in people.

33:17.167 --> 33:19.567
I just saw the bad.

33:20.267 --> 33:22.800
Grace: What happened to her?

33:22.833 --> 33:25.400
There I go being nosey again.

33:26.067 --> 33:29.133
Rick: I was a cop.

33:29.167 --> 33:31.433
Protect and serve.

33:31.467 --> 33:34.067
It was my job to protect her.

33:35.167 --> 33:37.167
Grace: Rick, pull over.

33:51.433 --> 33:54.500
Rick: We were working
this big case for a long time.

33:56.667 --> 33:58.667
We finally busted the guy.

34:00.233 --> 34:08.500
A real stand-up citizen,
Rotary Club, philanthropist,

34:08.533 --> 34:11.600
kids in Ivy League schools,
the works.

34:11.633 --> 34:13.300
Turns out he was also
responsible for half

34:13.333 --> 34:16.300
the drug trafficking
in the state.

34:16.333 --> 34:22.400
I got a promotion,
and he got 14 years.

34:23.833 --> 34:29.433
Instead of rotting
in a cell somewhere,

34:29.467 --> 34:32.333
he got cancer.

34:33.367 --> 34:37.033
He got it real bad too.

34:37.067 --> 34:40.233
So, they moved
him to a hospital.

34:40.267 --> 34:48.067
I knew it wasn't gonna take him
long to find a way out of there.

34:48.100 --> 34:52.200
Turns out I was the first person
he couldn't wait to see.

34:56.300 --> 34:58.667
I had scrimped and saved,

34:58.700 --> 35:01.533
doing everything to hide
it from Jenna.

35:01.567 --> 35:03.667
So, while I'm sitting
at a travel agency,

35:03.700 --> 35:07.267
booking the Paris trip
she always dreamed of,

35:07.300 --> 35:09.667
that dirtbag was coming for me.

35:10.333 --> 35:12.433
Rick: Babe?

35:13.200 --> 35:15.500
I got you a little surprise.

35:15.533 --> 35:18.300
I think you're gonna like it.

35:18.333 --> 35:21.033
I saw Luke playing ball
down the street,

35:21.067 --> 35:24.633
so I know that we are
all alone right now.

35:25.300 --> 35:27.467
Just the two of us, baby.

35:27.500 --> 35:31.300
Ooh, man, that turkey
smells fantastic.

35:32.567 --> 35:35.433
[Jenna gasping]

35:35.467 --> 35:37.200
Rick: Hey.

35:37.233 --> 35:39.167
Sam: Well, isn't that sweet?

35:39.200 --> 35:40.733
Go ahead and pull it!

35:40.767 --> 35:43.367
[coughing]

35:43.400 --> 35:45.133
Rick: Baby, go
out back right now.

35:45.167 --> 35:47.667
Sam: Honey,
you just stay right there.

35:49.833 --> 35:52.267
Sit down!

35:53.767 --> 35:55.533
Rick: She got nothing
to do with this, Jenkins.

35:55.567 --> 35:57.700
Sam: She's got everything
to do with this.

35:57.733 --> 36:04.100
My wife, my kids, my life,
you took 'em all from me!

36:04.533 --> 36:06.067
Rick: What do you want?

36:06.100 --> 36:08.533
Sam: What do I want?

36:08.567 --> 36:10.433
How about a cure for cancer?

36:10.467 --> 36:13.400
[coughing]

36:15.433 --> 36:17.467
I'm dying, detective.

36:17.500 --> 36:19.100
I'm gonna die
cold and alone,

36:19.133 --> 36:22.200
and I want you to know
what that feels like.

36:23.533 --> 36:25.167
What are you, a ninja?

36:25.200 --> 36:28.267
Keep moving towards me,
detective, I'm begging you.

36:28.300 --> 36:30.300
Rick: Turn around
right now and leave.

36:30.333 --> 36:31.767
No harm, no foul.

36:31.800 --> 36:33.467
Sam: Oh, really?

36:33.500 --> 36:35.400
No harm, no foul?

36:35.433 --> 36:37.733
[coughing]

36:37.767 --> 36:39.767
How about this for harm and--

36:39.800 --> 36:43.067
[timer dings]

36:43.100 --> 36:45.467
[gunshot firing]

36:46.133 --> 36:47.733
Rick: Three shots rang out.

36:47.767 --> 36:50.667
[gunshots firing]

36:55.167 --> 36:58.700
Rick: One went through
my knee,

36:58.733 --> 37:01.433
another one finished him off.

37:05.767 --> 37:13.033
I fell to the ground
and then I saw my wife,

37:13.067 --> 37:15.800
laying there on the ground.

37:15.833 --> 37:18.267
She was coughing.

37:18.300 --> 37:21.133
[Jenna coughing]

37:21.167 --> 37:23.133
Rick: Come here.
Come here.

37:23.167 --> 37:25.133
What's going on?
What's going on?

37:25.167 --> 37:26.567
What's going on?

37:26.600 --> 37:27.533
Jenna: I can't breathe.

37:27.567 --> 37:29.100
Rick: It's okay, baby.
It's gonna be fine.

37:29.133 --> 37:30.567
It's gonna be fine.
Just take it easy.

37:30.600 --> 37:32.233
Take it easy.

37:32.267 --> 37:33.700
Jenna: Promise me.

37:33.733 --> 37:35.267
Rick: Whatever you want.

37:35.300 --> 37:36.733
Whatever you want.

37:36.767 --> 37:40.533
Jenna: Make sure Luke knows
how much you love him.

37:42.433 --> 37:44.433
Rick: I promise you.

37:48.433 --> 37:50.267
Jenna: I love you.

37:50.300 --> 37:51.767
I love you.

37:51.800 --> 37:53.400
Rick: I love you.

37:53.433 --> 37:54.467
I love you.
Come on.

37:54.500 --> 37:57.067
Hey, stay with me, okay?

37:57.100 --> 38:00.067
Baby?
Baby?

38:00.100 --> 38:02.767
Baby?

38:02.800 --> 38:06.000
Rick: I failed.

38:06.800 --> 38:12.533
As a cop,
as a husband...

38:14.467 --> 38:17.333
...as a father.

38:20.067 --> 38:23.033
That was 5 years ago today.

38:25.200 --> 38:28.600
Grace: I'm so sorry.

38:29.333 --> 38:36.333
Rick: I've lived that day
over and over and over.

38:39.833 --> 38:43.267
Grace: It's never too late
to keep your promise.

38:47.367 --> 38:51.100
Rick: Let's get you home.

38:51.133 --> 39:01.167
[music]

39:01.167 --> 39:06.133
[music]

39:06.233 --> 39:16.267
[music]

39:16.267 --> 39:21.133
[music]

39:21.233 --> 39:32.000
[music]

39:32.100 --> 39:34.033
Grace: Rick, can you
stop the car?

39:34.067 --> 39:36.233
Rick: What is it?

39:49.100 --> 39:52.367
Grace, what's going on?

39:55.067 --> 39:56.500
Time's a-ticking.

39:56.533 --> 39:58.367
Grace: Do you think it's true
that God has chosen

39:58.400 --> 40:02.233
that one special person
for each of us?

40:02.267 --> 40:03.733
That one person
that's meant to be with us

40:03.767 --> 40:05.600
for the rest of our lives.

40:05.633 --> 40:07.300
Rick: Here we go again
with the God stuff.

40:07.333 --> 40:09.500
Can we just--

40:09.533 --> 40:12.033
Grace?

40:16.367 --> 40:17.733
What are you doing, Grace?

40:17.767 --> 40:19.633
What--not--

40:19.667 --> 40:21.133
Grace: Come on, Rick.

40:21.167 --> 40:22.600
I can see a glimmer
of hope in you.

40:22.633 --> 40:25.200
You don't have to be
the tough one all the time.

40:27.833 --> 40:30.033
Rick: Grace?

40:32.567 --> 40:35.267
She did it again.

40:45.533 --> 40:48.333
Grace: Do you believe
in love at first sight?

40:48.700 --> 40:50.300
I used to work at this
little coffee shop

40:50.333 --> 40:52.533
not too far from here,

40:52.567 --> 40:56.200
and this tall,
handsome Marine walks in.

40:56.233 --> 40:58.700
He sits at the counter.

40:58.733 --> 41:01.633
I'm so nervous I could
barely pour his coffee.

41:01.667 --> 41:04.367
Rick: What are we doing here,
Grace?

41:04.400 --> 41:06.733
Grace: It was love
at first sight for him.

41:06.767 --> 41:08.800
He proposed on our first date.

41:08.833 --> 41:10.467
I mean, he didn't have
a ring or anything,

41:10.500 --> 41:17.067
but he knew I was the one,
and I knew he was the one too.

41:17.100 --> 41:18.667
Rick: And then you came here
and learned to dance

41:18.700 --> 41:20.400
and wowed everyone
at your wedding, right?

41:20.433 --> 41:23.533
Grace: Wow, that was so mean.

41:24.100 --> 41:26.533
Did you really have to say that?

41:29.433 --> 41:30.700
Rick: You think
you're the only one

41:30.733 --> 41:33.433
with special moments, Grace?

41:33.467 --> 41:36.600
My wife and I came
to this same studio.

41:36.633 --> 41:39.367
This is where she taught me
how to dance.

41:39.400 --> 41:42.400
And yes, we wowed everybody
at our wedding,

41:42.433 --> 41:46.467
and we vowed that we
would never stop dancing.

41:46.500 --> 41:49.767
And then your God,
in his infinite wisdom,

41:49.800 --> 41:53.667
took her from me,

41:53.700 --> 41:56.733
and we're never gonna
dance together again.

41:58.600 --> 42:01.267
How's that for a happy ending?

42:02.567 --> 42:04.333
Grace: I'm so sorry.

42:04.367 --> 42:06.733
Rick: Sorry for what?

42:06.767 --> 42:08.767
You don't have to be sorry.

42:08.800 --> 42:11.733
You get to go have Thanksgiving
with your family, and I can't.

42:11.767 --> 42:14.267
Now, can we just go
to the car, please?

42:15.400 --> 42:18.133
Grace: Was it love
at first sight for you too?

42:18.167 --> 42:19.433
Rick: Does it matter?

42:19.467 --> 42:22.000
Grace: Maybe.
Was it?

42:23.633 --> 42:25.100
Rick, was it?

42:25.133 --> 42:27.600
Rick: Yes!

42:29.300 --> 42:30.733
My heart was beating
out of my chest

42:30.767 --> 42:33.200
the first moment I saw her.

42:33.233 --> 42:34.633
Grace: Then maybe
it is true that God has

42:34.667 --> 42:38.067
that one special person
for us.

42:38.100 --> 42:41.333
And it doesn't matter
how long we spend with them.

42:41.367 --> 42:45.567
What matters is how we spend
the time we had with them.

42:46.167 --> 42:51.100
Maybe that's why God
put us together today,

42:51.133 --> 42:56.167
to teach us how to appreciate
every single moment we have.

43:06.400 --> 43:09.100
Rick: What are you--

43:09.667 --> 43:11.700
No, I'm not much
of a dancer anymore.

43:11.733 --> 43:14.700
I've got that bum leg, remember?

43:14.733 --> 43:17.633
Grace: Come on.
No one's watching.

43:20.667 --> 43:22.200
Rick: Yeah.

43:22.233 --> 43:23.633
Jenna: Dance with me,
officer.

43:23.667 --> 43:24.500
Rick: Not now.
Not now.

43:24.533 --> 43:26.200
I gotta review this case
for the morning.

43:26.233 --> 43:27.500
Jenna: Shh.

43:27.533 --> 43:29.433
The case'll still be there.
This moment won't.

43:29.467 --> 43:32.033
Rick: It's a big case.
What are you doing?

43:32.067 --> 43:33.500
What are you doing?
I gotta work.

43:33.533 --> 43:35.233
I gotta work.

43:35.267 --> 43:36.633
I can't dance right now.

43:36.667 --> 43:39.400
Jenna: Yes, you can.

