46:14.867 --> 46:21.267
* I'll follow you
the way home *

46:22.633 --> 46:28.433
* I'll follow you
the way home *

46:29.200 --> 46:34.567
* I'll follow you
the way home *

46:35.333 --> 46:40.167
* I'll follow you
the way home **

46:45.367 --> 46:48.267
Rick: Your God's not making
this any easier on us.

46:51.733 --> 46:53.433
It's dead.

46:53.467 --> 46:55.600
This old piece of junk is dead.

46:55.633 --> 46:57.500
Grace: We could always
go walking.

46:57.533 --> 46:58.700
Rick: Walking?

46:58.733 --> 46:59.700
No.
You know what?

46:59.733 --> 47:00.667
I'm just gonna go ask--

47:00.700 --> 47:02.400
Grace: No, let's go walking.
It'll be fun.

47:02.433 --> 47:04.167
It's a great day.
I'm gonna grab my stuff.

47:04.200 --> 47:05.167
Rick: You wanna walk?

47:05.200 --> 47:07.200
Grace: Yeah!

47:12.500 --> 47:14.067
Rick: I mean--

47:14.100 --> 47:16.233
Grace: Thank you.
Let's go.

47:17.333 --> 47:21.267
Rick: Okay.
Let's walk.

47:21.300 --> 47:31.333
[music]

47:31.333 --> 47:36.300
[music]

47:36.400 --> 47:42.467
[music]

47:42.567 --> 47:44.433
Rick: Okay, so I think
if we take a left here

47:44.467 --> 47:45.367
and we go around the bend,

47:45.400 --> 47:47.333
we'll get straight through
to your house.

47:47.367 --> 47:50.333
Grace: Isn't there another way
we can go?

47:50.367 --> 47:51.800
Rick: Well, this'll be
the quickest way.

47:51.833 --> 47:53.333
Grace: I think it's
a dead end anyway,

47:53.367 --> 47:55.600
so we can just go
somewhere else.

47:55.633 --> 47:58.100
Rick: Grace, what's up?

47:58.133 --> 48:00.400
Grace: My in-laws live
up there.

48:00.433 --> 48:01.667
Rick: Oh!

48:01.700 --> 48:04.233
Well, maybe they can
help us out with my car.

48:04.267 --> 48:06.400
Grace: No, they moved
a long time ago.

48:06.433 --> 48:08.600
Can we just take another street?

48:08.633 --> 48:10.567
Please.

48:10.600 --> 48:12.267
Rick: I understand.

48:12.300 --> 48:14.333
You know, I mean, so you have
some problems with your in-laws.

48:14.367 --> 48:16.167
Join the club.

48:16.200 --> 48:17.800
Grace: I didn't say that.

48:17.833 --> 48:20.333
They were wonderful.

48:20.367 --> 48:30.400
[music]

48:30.400 --> 48:35.367
[music]

48:35.467 --> 48:45.500
[music]

48:45.500 --> 48:50.367
[music]

48:50.567 --> 48:53.600
David: Can you show me
how the lights work?

48:54.333 --> 48:56.333
[truck beeping]

48:56.367 --> 48:58.167
David: Awesome.

48:58.200 --> 49:00.667
Hey, you wanna play
hide and seek?

49:01.300 --> 49:03.267
Okay, go hide.

49:05.767 --> 49:08.267
Grace: Don't go too far.

49:08.300 --> 49:09.767
David: He's fine.

49:09.800 --> 49:12.167
Grace: Tommy was
everything to them.

49:12.200 --> 49:14.033
He was their one
connection to their son

49:14.067 --> 49:16.733
while he was serving
in Afghanistan.

49:16.767 --> 49:20.133
Rick: So, your husband
served overseas?

49:20.167 --> 49:23.533
Grace: I would Skype with him
whenever we could.

49:23.567 --> 49:30.533
Tommy was so proud of his daddy,
and Daddy loved him to pieces.

49:32.333 --> 49:35.067
David: Here I come!

49:38.267 --> 49:40.167
Grace: So, how was your trip?

49:40.200 --> 49:41.467
We so wanted to go.

49:41.500 --> 49:42.800
Bella: Oh, it was wonderful.

49:42.833 --> 49:44.467
You two have got
to join us next time.

49:44.500 --> 49:46.233
Grace: I know.

49:46.267 --> 49:48.100
David: I can't find Tommy.

49:48.133 --> 49:49.500
Grace: What?

49:49.533 --> 49:51.500
Tommy?

49:51.533 --> 49:53.600
Bella: Well, he can't
have gone far.

49:54.467 --> 49:56.633
Grace: Tommy?

50:01.233 --> 50:03.700
Tommy?
Tommy!

50:11.367 --> 50:13.100
Grace: I couldn't breathe.

50:13.133 --> 50:14.767
Grace: Tommy!

50:14.800 --> 50:17.533
Grace: I couldn't move.

50:20.733 --> 50:22.767
You're not the only one that
thinks they failed to take care

50:22.800 --> 50:25.633
of the ones they loved.

50:26.167 --> 50:29.133
I've struggled with that
for so many years,

50:29.167 --> 50:32.567
blaming myself every day.

50:32.600 --> 50:35.400
Rick: Grace, that
wasn't your fault.

50:37.133 --> 50:40.567
Grace: Faith is believing
in the things we can't see.

50:40.600 --> 50:43.567
I'm just trusting it's all
part of a better plan

50:43.600 --> 50:46.500
and that there's
a deeper meaning.

50:46.533 --> 50:48.200
Rick: I gave up trying
to figure that out

50:48.233 --> 50:49.433
a long time ago.

50:49.467 --> 50:50.733
Grace: You can't give up.

50:50.767 --> 50:52.633
Rick, you can't.

50:52.667 --> 50:56.533
You have to trust that God
knows better than we do.

50:56.567 --> 50:58.600
Rick: I've been dead
inside for years, Grace.

50:58.633 --> 51:00.467
There's no hope for me.

51:00.500 --> 51:05.467
Grace: I was in the same
exact dark hole that you're in.

51:05.500 --> 51:07.467
There is hope.

51:07.500 --> 51:09.767
Believe me.

51:12.667 --> 51:14.367
Rick: Come on.

51:14.400 --> 51:16.333
We should get going.
It's gonna get cold out soon.

51:16.367 --> 51:17.600
Grace: Yeah.

51:17.633 --> 51:19.167
Thank you, Rick.

51:19.200 --> 51:20.267
Rick: For what?

51:20.300 --> 51:24.433
Grace: For driving me,
for walking with me, listening.

51:26.433 --> 51:28.367
Rick: It's Thanksgiving,
right?

51:28.400 --> 51:30.300
Grace: That's right.

51:30.333 --> 51:33.000
Rick: Come on.

51:39.733 --> 51:41.133
Anne: Luke?

51:41.167 --> 51:42.700
Honey, it's time to eat.

51:42.733 --> 51:45.267
Luke: Be right there.

51:54.333 --> 51:56.167
Anne: I hope you're hungry!

51:56.200 --> 51:58.033
Luke: Been smelling turkey
all day, Grandma.

51:58.067 --> 51:59.367
I'm starving.

51:59.400 --> 52:00.467
Anne: Well, good.

52:00.500 --> 52:02.133
'Cause we've got
some eating to do.

52:02.167 --> 52:03.733
Hey, hey, hey!

52:03.767 --> 52:06.233
Aren't you forgetting
something, young man?

52:09.233 --> 52:12.667
Dear Lord, we thank you
for this special day

52:12.700 --> 52:14.533
and for all
of our blessings.

52:14.567 --> 52:17.567
And Lord, we just ask you
to watch over those

52:17.600 --> 52:22.033
who can't be here with us today
to share in them.

52:22.067 --> 52:24.700
In your name, amen.

52:28.267 --> 52:30.333
Luke?

52:30.367 --> 52:32.667
Luke: Amen.

52:33.267 --> 52:36.467
Anne: So, have you heard
from your father today?

52:36.500 --> 52:39.600
I left a message for him
on his machine.

52:39.633 --> 52:41.200
Luke: Yeah, Grandma.

52:41.233 --> 52:42.800
He should be here any sec.

52:42.833 --> 52:44.333
Anne: Well, you never know.

52:44.367 --> 52:45.767
It could happen.

52:45.800 --> 52:48.333
Luke: Grandma, every holiday
you set an extra seat,

52:48.367 --> 52:51.700
and every year it
stays that way.

52:51.733 --> 52:56.200
Anne: Well, I guess I just
can't give up on him.

52:56.233 --> 53:00.800
Luke: Can we please just eat
and not talk about it?

53:00.833 --> 53:03.400
Anne: Of course.

53:11.700 --> 53:15.267
Luke: Grandma, do you mind
if I eat in my room?

53:17.467 --> 53:22.633
Anne: You know, it's just
taking him time, Luke.

53:22.667 --> 53:25.767
And it's taking more time
than we would like,

53:25.800 --> 53:27.533
but he'll come around.

53:27.567 --> 53:29.500
You'll see.

53:29.533 --> 53:32.800
Luke: Does it even matter
anymore, really?

53:32.833 --> 53:36.033
Anne: Baby, of course
it matters.

53:36.067 --> 53:39.033
Your father loves you.

53:39.067 --> 53:41.200
Luke: Yeah?

53:41.233 --> 53:44.133
Well, he's got a funny way
of showing it.

53:44.167 --> 53:46.067
Can I?

53:46.100 --> 53:48.533
Anne: Okay.

53:49.667 --> 53:51.600
You have enough there?

53:51.633 --> 53:54.067
Luke: Yeah.
Thanks, Grandma.

53:54.100 --> 53:56.567
Anne: Okay.

53:57.500 --> 53:59.267
All right, well be sure
to save room

53:59.300 --> 54:01.033
for that cherry pie I made you.

54:01.067 --> 54:02.367
Luke: I will.

54:02.400 --> 54:05.100
Anne: I made whipped cream!

54:07.667 --> 54:10.200
[sighing]

54:11.700 --> 54:13.800
Grace: Mmm, I think
I just got a whiff of turkey

54:13.833 --> 54:15.633
coming out of the oven.

54:15.667 --> 54:17.300
Do you like turkey?

54:17.333 --> 54:19.100
Rick: Yeah, I guess so.

54:19.133 --> 54:21.333
I mean, I actually--

54:21.367 --> 54:25.467
I haven't sat down for
a turkey dinner in a long time.

54:26.233 --> 54:27.567
Grace: Come
to think of it,

54:27.600 --> 54:29.433
I can't remember the last time
I had turkey either.

54:29.467 --> 54:30.567
Rick: Yeah?

54:30.600 --> 54:32.167
Well, I'm sure
your family'll have

54:32.200 --> 54:35.167
a nice turkey dinner
waiting for you.

54:38.767 --> 54:40.100
Grace: You okay?

54:40.133 --> 54:41.633
Rick: Yeah, I'm good.
You?

54:41.667 --> 54:43.267
Grace: Yeah.

54:43.300 --> 54:44.800
I'm sorry I've ruined your day

54:44.833 --> 54:48.067
with this crazy little
journey of mine.

54:48.100 --> 54:51.600
Rick: Trust me, I had
nothing better to do.

54:55.500 --> 54:57.500
You know what?

54:57.533 --> 55:01.133
Why don't we go warm up
inside there for a minute?

55:12.633 --> 55:15.200
Grace: Cute little church,
isn't it?

55:15.233 --> 55:17.200
Rick: Yeah, if you say so.

55:17.233 --> 55:18.733
Grace: What are you doing?

55:18.767 --> 55:20.333
Rick: I'm just gonna see
if it's open.

55:20.367 --> 55:21.500
Grace: It's Thanksgiving.
It's gonna be closed.

55:21.533 --> 55:23.333
Rick: I'm gonna jiggle it
and see.

55:23.367 --> 55:25.367
It's been working for you.

55:29.333 --> 55:32.233
[Grace laughing]

55:46.133 --> 55:49.033
Grace: It's so nice.

55:52.200 --> 56:02.200
[music]

56:02.300 --> 56:07.433
[music]

56:07.533 --> 56:10.333
Rick: Not really much
warmer than outside, is it?

56:10.367 --> 56:13.400
Grace: Oh, I'm fine.

56:13.433 --> 56:16.267
I just haven't sat in one
of these pews in a while.

56:16.300 --> 56:18.600
I miss it.

56:18.633 --> 56:20.400
Rick: You?

56:20.433 --> 56:23.767
Now, see, I would
take you for a regular

56:23.800 --> 56:27.467
for this kind of thing.

56:27.500 --> 56:29.700
Grace: I am, in my heart.

56:29.733 --> 56:33.567
I just haven't been able to come
to service in a long time.

56:35.367 --> 56:37.333
Rick: The whole no car thing?

56:37.367 --> 56:39.433
[Grace laughing]
No, silly.

56:39.467 --> 56:43.700
But you're right, a car would've
been very helpful today.

56:46.300 --> 56:50.067
So, did your wife go to church?

56:52.233 --> 56:53.700
I'm sorry, you don't have
to talk about it.

56:53.733 --> 56:55.333
Rick: No, no, it's fine.

56:55.367 --> 56:57.167
Yes.

56:57.200 --> 57:01.567
Yep, she always came to church
and I would come with her,

57:01.600 --> 57:03.733
you know, 'cause she
wanted me to.

57:03.767 --> 57:07.233
And my son seemed to like it,
so you know,

57:07.267 --> 57:10.600
that made her happy.

57:10.633 --> 57:13.367
Grace: You're
a kind man, Rick.

57:13.400 --> 57:16.433
Any other guy would just sit on
the couch and watch a game

57:16.467 --> 57:18.367
or whatever they do.

57:18.400 --> 57:20.467
Rick: No, it made her happy.
That's the only reason.

57:20.500 --> 57:24.600
I haven't stepped foot
inside a church in 5 years.

57:25.333 --> 57:28.300
Grace: I understand.

57:30.300 --> 57:36.467
Sometimes it's hard
trusting that his ways

57:36.500 --> 57:39.633
are higher than ours.

57:42.500 --> 57:44.433
Rick: You know, we should
probably get a move on,

57:44.467 --> 57:47.800
only 'cause it's only gonna get
colder as the night goes on.

57:47.833 --> 57:51.000
Grace: Do you mind
if I pray before we go?

57:54.400 --> 57:57.000
Rick: Sure.

57:58.467 --> 58:00.800
Grace: You can join me
if you'd like.

58:00.833 --> 58:06.233
Rick: No, no.
I'm good right here.

58:15.433 --> 58:21.333
Grace: Lord, I was in
a dark place this morning.

58:21.367 --> 58:26.300
Forgive me
for not trusting you.

58:26.333 --> 58:28.367
You sent me
to the middle of nowhere,

58:28.400 --> 58:33.567
and I met
this kind man, Rick.

58:33.600 --> 58:38.233
And you made us meet at
that very moment for a reason.

58:38.267 --> 58:42.133
And I pray that you
soften his heart.

58:42.167 --> 58:44.567
He's had a rough go of it.

58:44.600 --> 58:48.133
And I pray that you give him
understanding and peace

58:48.167 --> 58:54.167
so we can continue our time
together today, amen.

59:00.133 --> 59:10.133
[music]

59:10.233 --> 59:17.300
[music]

59:17.400 --> 59:20.300
I hope you didn't mind me
adding you to the prayer.

59:20.767 --> 59:22.267
Rick: No.

59:22.300 --> 59:24.200
No, it's fine.

59:24.233 --> 59:26.400
It's fine.
Come on.

59:29.767 --> 59:31.633
[Grace gasping]
Wait!

59:31.667 --> 59:33.167
Rick: What?

59:33.200 --> 59:34.433
Grace: I left
my purse inside.

59:34.467 --> 59:37.000
Rick: I'll get it for you.

59:51.233 --> 1:00:01.267
[music]

1:00:01.267 --> 1:00:06.233
[music]

1:00:06.333 --> 1:00:16.233
[music]

1:00:16.333 --> 1:00:26.200
[music]

1:00:26.300 --> 1:00:32.600
Rick: God, if you're up there...

1:00:39.700 --> 1:00:41.700
...please help me.

1:00:56.600 --> 1:00:58.300
Grace: Thank you.

1:00:58.333 --> 1:01:00.267
Rick: You're welcome.

1:01:02.400 --> 1:01:04.233
Grace: We can
cut through here.

1:01:04.267 --> 1:01:06.300
Rick: Okay.

1:01:12.700 --> 1:01:13.800
Rick: Hey!

1:01:13.833 --> 1:01:15.100
Where are we going?

1:01:15.133 --> 1:01:16.167
Grace: Shortcut!

1:01:16.200 --> 1:01:17.200
Rick: Shortcut?

1:01:17.233 --> 1:01:18.633
Are you sure?

1:01:18.667 --> 1:01:21.600
I mean--like I have a choice.

1:01:24.767 --> 1:01:26.367
Grace!

1:01:27.100 --> 1:01:28.233
Grace!

1:01:28.267 --> 1:01:29.433
Where are we going now?

1:01:29.467 --> 1:01:30.767
Grace: I'm just trying
to save some time,

1:01:30.800 --> 1:01:32.100
get you home to your son.

1:01:32.133 --> 1:01:33.267
Rick: I was thinking
about that.

1:01:33.300 --> 1:01:35.133
You know, Grace,
my son is--

1:01:35.167 --> 1:01:36.367
It's just not the best--

1:01:36.400 --> 1:01:37.667
Grace: I'm listening.

1:01:37.700 --> 1:01:39.133
Rick: I know you say
you're listening,

1:01:39.167 --> 1:01:40.467
but you're not.

1:01:40.500 --> 1:01:41.700
You're not really listening.
You're just walking.

1:01:41.733 --> 1:01:43.067
You just keep walking.

1:01:43.100 --> 1:01:44.333
Grace!

1:01:44.367 --> 1:01:45.767
Hey!
Grace!

1:01:45.800 --> 1:01:47.633
Can you slow down
a tad please?

1:01:47.667 --> 1:01:49.133
Grace: Sorry.

1:01:49.167 --> 1:01:50.400
I don't know what's
gotten into me.

1:01:50.433 --> 1:01:53.133
I think it's still open space.

1:01:53.167 --> 1:01:56.467
Rick: Hey, that's
my old ball field.

1:01:56.500 --> 1:01:58.067
I played little league there.

1:01:58.100 --> 1:01:59.333
Grace: It was?

1:01:59.367 --> 1:02:00.500
Rick: Yes.

1:02:00.533 --> 1:02:01.733
Wow, it's changed a lot.

1:02:01.767 --> 1:02:03.800
But, oh man, back in the day,
we had dugouts

1:02:03.833 --> 1:02:05.467
on either side
of the backstop

1:02:05.500 --> 1:02:07.533
and the bleachers
were over in the corner.

1:02:07.567 --> 1:02:10.333
My mom and pop,
they never missed a game.

1:02:10.367 --> 1:02:12.467
Grace: Really?

1:02:13.267 --> 1:02:16.267
Rick: It's been a long time
since I've seen it.

1:02:34.200 --> 1:02:38.533
I would bring my son here before
he was even old enough to play.

1:02:40.633 --> 1:02:43.200
He couldn't wait.

1:02:44.367 --> 1:02:45.600
Grace: I'm sure you were
in those bleachers

1:02:45.633 --> 1:02:50.133
watching every minute of your
boy playing ball, weren't you?

1:02:51.400 --> 1:02:53.733
Rick: No, I wasn't, Grace.

1:02:53.767 --> 1:02:56.033
I was always too busy.

1:02:56.067 --> 1:02:58.733
Grace: Oh.
I'm sorry.

1:03:00.067 --> 1:03:02.567
Rick: He would always beg me
to play ball with him.

1:03:04.500 --> 1:03:08.267
He would wear that little glove
and he would say,

1:03:08.300 --> 1:03:11.667
"Daddy, you play
catch with me?"

1:03:11.700 --> 1:03:14.567
"Not today, buddy.

1:03:14.600 --> 1:03:17.700
Daddy's gotta go catch
some bad guys."

1:03:18.633 --> 1:03:21.600
Grace: At least he's still
got you around.

1:03:21.633 --> 1:03:27.200
Rick: When his mother--
when Jenna was killed,

1:03:27.233 --> 1:03:30.533
it was just a bad time.

1:03:30.567 --> 1:03:32.567
I was--

1:03:37.167 --> 1:03:39.500
He's been with my mom
ever since.

1:03:39.533 --> 1:03:41.167
Grace: But it's been 5 years.

1:03:41.200 --> 1:03:42.367
You still see him, though.

1:03:42.400 --> 1:03:43.467
Rick: Of course I see him.

1:03:43.500 --> 1:03:45.333
I see him every day.

1:03:45.367 --> 1:03:47.033
He doesn't know I'm there.

1:03:47.067 --> 1:03:49.467
Grace: He doesn't know
you're there?

1:03:49.500 --> 1:03:53.267
Rick: When I drive by,
I see him playing ball

1:03:53.300 --> 1:03:56.567
and hanging with his friends.

1:03:57.433 --> 1:04:01.067
Grace: Rick,
you can't do that.

1:04:01.100 --> 1:04:03.267
A son needs his father.

1:04:03.300 --> 1:04:05.500
It's not fair for you
to stay away.

1:04:05.533 --> 1:04:06.767
Rick: He's doing great.

1:04:06.800 --> 1:04:08.667
He's a good kid.

1:04:08.700 --> 1:04:10.333
He's better off without me.

1:04:10.367 --> 1:04:12.367
Grace: You don't believe that.

1:04:12.400 --> 1:04:15.400
I'm sure he misses you
as much as you miss him.

1:04:16.167 --> 1:04:18.300
Rick: I wouldn't know
what to say.

1:04:18.333 --> 1:04:19.600
Grace: Just tell him
the truth.

1:04:19.633 --> 1:04:22.000
Tell him you love him.

1:04:23.467 --> 1:04:26.300
Rick: It's too late
for that, Grace.

1:04:27.100 --> 1:04:30.033
Grace: Rick,
if you're still breathing,

1:04:30.067 --> 1:04:33.300
it's never too late to tell
your son that you love him.

1:04:33.833 --> 1:04:36.333
I can't do that anymore.

1:04:36.367 --> 1:04:39.233
You don't understand how much
I long to hold my boy,

1:04:39.267 --> 1:04:40.600
to tell him that I love him,

1:04:40.633 --> 1:04:43.533
to tell him that I'm gonna
be there for him.

1:04:43.567 --> 1:04:47.233
You still have time.
Please.

1:04:49.767 --> 1:04:53.367
Rick: You're a special woman,
Grace.

1:04:53.400 --> 1:04:55.700
Grace: You're a special man,
Rick.

1:04:55.733 --> 1:04:59.667
And you're a father
that needs his son.

1:04:59.700 --> 1:05:02.633
Now, go out there
and make it right.

1:05:06.433 --> 1:05:08.600
Come on.

1:05:12.800 --> 1:05:16.433
Grace: So, is Rick short for
something like Richard, Ricky?

1:05:16.467 --> 1:05:18.600
Rick: Yeah.
Yeah, it's short for Ricky.

1:05:18.633 --> 1:05:20.500
My parents were born in Cuba.

1:05:20.533 --> 1:05:22.667
They loved watching
"I Love Lucy."

1:05:22.700 --> 1:05:24.233
[Grace laughing]
Really?

1:05:24.267 --> 1:05:28.100
Rick: No, not really,
gullible.

1:05:28.133 --> 1:05:33.367
No, it's short for Richard
in a long line of Richards.

1:05:33.400 --> 1:05:35.700
What about you, huh?

1:05:35.733 --> 1:05:37.500
Is your name short for Gracie?

1:05:37.533 --> 1:05:39.167
Grace: Oh, now you're
just making fun of me.

1:05:39.200 --> 1:05:40.400
Rick: I'm sorry.

1:05:40.433 --> 1:05:41.733
[laughing]

1:05:41.767 --> 1:05:43.167
Grace: No,
when my parents met,

1:05:43.200 --> 1:05:45.467
they were missionaries.

1:05:45.500 --> 1:05:47.633
They wanted to remind me
every day how to live my life

1:05:47.667 --> 1:05:50.667
and never forgetting
God's grace.

1:05:51.400 --> 1:05:52.800
Rick: That fits you.

1:05:52.833 --> 1:05:54.133
Grace: Thank you.

1:05:54.167 --> 1:05:55.100
I'm gonna take that
as a compliment.

1:05:55.133 --> 1:05:57.467
Rick: You should take that
as a compliment.

1:05:57.500 --> 1:05:59.333
So, is that who
we're gonna go see?

1:05:59.367 --> 1:06:00.733
Grace: Who?

1:06:00.767 --> 1:06:03.267
Rick: Well, you know,
today, this whole journey.

1:06:03.300 --> 1:06:05.500
I mean, we're gonna
go see your parents?

1:06:05.533 --> 1:06:07.100
Grace: Oh, no.

1:06:07.133 --> 1:06:08.667
My mom, she died
a couple of years ago.

1:06:08.700 --> 1:06:12.633
And well, my dad,
you know that story.

1:06:13.267 --> 1:06:16.100
Rick: Sorry.

1:06:16.133 --> 1:06:18.333
I really don't know
how you do it, Grace.

1:06:18.367 --> 1:06:19.700
Grace: What's that?

1:06:19.733 --> 1:06:21.500
Rick: The way you just--
you keep the faith,

1:06:21.533 --> 1:06:27.567
I mean, despite all these sad
things that've happened to you.

1:06:27.600 --> 1:06:30.400
I mean, next thing,
you're gonna tell me

1:06:30.433 --> 1:06:34.400
you're dying of some rare
tropical disease or something.

1:06:34.433 --> 1:06:37.633
[Grace laughing]
Yeah, that would be something.

1:06:46.233 --> 1:06:48.567
Rick: What's the rush, Grace?

1:06:48.600 --> 1:06:50.133
How did we get here?

1:06:50.167 --> 1:06:51.733
Grace: Come on,
we're almost there.

1:06:51.767 --> 1:06:53.300
Rick: No.

1:06:53.333 --> 1:06:55.467
No, I don't wanna
go this way, Grace.

1:06:55.500 --> 1:06:57.367
Grace!

1:06:58.300 --> 1:07:00.667
Grace?

1:07:09.700 --> 1:07:12.100
Grace: We're here.

1:07:12.433 --> 1:07:13.800
It's Thanksgiving, Rick.

1:07:13.833 --> 1:07:17.133
What better time than now?

1:07:17.167 --> 1:07:19.033
Rick: I don't think
I can do it, Grace.

1:07:19.067 --> 1:07:20.567
Grace: Your son needs you.
You need your son.

1:07:20.600 --> 1:07:22.633
Of course you can do it.

1:07:22.667 --> 1:07:24.700
Rick: What if he hates me?

1:07:24.733 --> 1:07:27.067
Grace: That's not possible.

1:07:40.833 --> 1:07:43.233
Rick: Okay.

1:07:46.367 --> 1:07:48.633
Rick: Ma?

1:07:48.667 --> 1:07:51.400
Anne: I knew it!

1:07:51.433 --> 1:07:53.633
I just knew it!

1:07:56.367 --> 1:07:58.167
Rick: Happy Thanksgiving,
Mom.

1:07:58.200 --> 1:08:00.333
Anne: Yes it is.

1:08:00.367 --> 1:08:02.133
Oh my goodness,
where are my manners?

1:08:02.167 --> 1:08:03.300
I'm Anne.

1:08:03.333 --> 1:08:04.767
Grace: Grace.

1:08:04.800 --> 1:08:06.200
Anne: Well,
that's a lovely name.

1:08:06.233 --> 1:08:07.367
Grace: Thank you.

1:08:07.400 --> 1:08:09.033
Anne: You should've told me
you were bringing a guest.

1:08:09.067 --> 1:08:10.633
I'm a mess.

1:08:10.667 --> 1:08:12.200
My goodness, you're cold as ice.

1:08:12.233 --> 1:08:13.200
Come in.
Come in.

1:08:13.233 --> 1:08:14.467
Are y'all hungry?

1:08:14.500 --> 1:08:15.633
Grace: I'm starving.

1:08:15.667 --> 1:08:16.500
Anne: I've got so much food.

1:08:16.533 --> 1:08:18.167
Please, come on,
I'll warm something up.

1:08:18.200 --> 1:08:19.167
Rick: Mom.
Mom.

1:08:19.200 --> 1:08:20.533
Anne: What?

1:08:20.567 --> 1:08:21.733
Rick: Is Luke here?

1:08:21.767 --> 1:08:24.167
Anne: Well, he's next door,
honey, playing with his friends.

1:08:24.200 --> 1:08:26.700
But you know, he'll be back
within the hour.

1:08:26.733 --> 1:08:29.100
So, please, come and eat.

1:08:29.133 --> 1:08:31.433
Oh my goodness!

1:08:42.300 --> 1:08:43.700
Anne: So, tell me,
how long have you two

1:08:43.733 --> 1:08:46.167
been seeing each other?

1:08:46.200 --> 1:08:47.500
Rick: Oh, what was it?

1:08:47.533 --> 1:08:50.500
It was, like, noon?

1:08:50.533 --> 1:08:52.367
Grace: I think
it was more like 1.

1:08:52.400 --> 1:08:54.100
Rick: Was it 1?
It was closer to 1.

1:08:54.133 --> 1:08:56.133
Anne: Well, you're crazy.

1:08:58.200 --> 1:09:08.233
[music]

1:09:08.233 --> 1:09:13.200
[music]

1:09:13.300 --> 1:09:24.233
[music]

1:09:24.333 --> 1:09:25.467
Anne: Here you go.

1:09:25.500 --> 1:09:26.667
Ladies first.

1:09:26.700 --> 1:09:28.100
Grace: Thank you!

1:09:28.133 --> 1:09:28.967
Rick: Absolutely.
Mom, amazing.

1:09:29.000 --> 1:09:30.567
I don't know if I can
eat this but--

1:09:30.600 --> 1:09:32.233
Anne: Well, do me
a favor and try, okay?

1:09:32.267 --> 1:09:33.767
Rick: Yes.
Yes.

1:09:33.800 --> 1:09:35.333
Grace: I can't remember
the last time

1:09:35.367 --> 1:09:36.467
I had homemade pie.

1:09:36.500 --> 1:09:37.567
It's so good.

1:09:37.600 --> 1:09:40.267
Anne: Well, there's plenty more
where that came from.

1:09:49.667 --> 1:09:52.167
Rick: Hey, Son.

1:09:55.800 --> 1:09:58.333
Luke: What are
you doing here?

1:09:58.733 --> 1:10:02.333
Rick: Wow, look at you.

1:10:02.367 --> 1:10:04.400
You're growing up fast.

1:10:04.433 --> 1:10:07.500
Luke: Yeah, if you
call 5 years fast.

1:10:11.833 --> 1:10:14.400
Rick: We got you
a little something.

1:10:14.433 --> 1:10:18.167
I don't know if
you remember this.

1:10:20.467 --> 1:10:24.233
Luke: That supposed to make
everything better?

1:10:24.267 --> 1:10:28.700
You think we can just hug it out
and pretend you're my dad again?

1:10:28.733 --> 1:10:30.467
Rick: That would be nice.

1:10:30.500 --> 1:10:32.700
Luke: It's not happening!

1:10:33.500 --> 1:10:36.267
Thanks for dropping by, Dad.

1:10:36.300 --> 1:10:38.367
See you again in
another 5 years.

1:10:38.400 --> 1:10:40.133
Anne: Luke, honey,
why don't you just sit down

1:10:40.167 --> 1:10:41.567
and have some pie with us?

1:10:41.600 --> 1:10:43.567
Rick: Luke.

1:10:43.600 --> 1:10:45.700
Luke: Just leave.

1:10:45.733 --> 1:10:48.200
We're better off without you.

1:10:51.833 --> 1:10:52.800
Rick: He hates me.

1:10:52.833 --> 1:10:54.233
Anne: No, no.

1:10:54.267 --> 1:10:56.333
He just needs time,
like you did.

1:10:56.367 --> 1:10:58.400
Just don't give up so easy.

1:10:58.433 --> 1:11:01.067
It's his turn now.

1:11:03.767 --> 1:11:06.200
Grace: I'm so proud of you.

1:11:26.667 --> 1:11:36.700
[music]

1:11:36.700 --> 1:11:41.667
[music]

1:11:41.767 --> 1:11:52.000
[music]

1:11:52.000 --> 1:11:56.667
[music]

1:11:56.767 --> 1:12:03.667
[music]

1:12:03.767 --> 1:12:06.400
[knocking]

1:12:06.433 --> 1:12:09.033
Rick: Luke?

1:12:11.100 --> 1:12:14.133
[knocking]

1:12:14.167 --> 1:12:16.533
Rick: Luke?

1:12:21.433 --> 1:12:23.433
Look, bud.

1:12:25.267 --> 1:12:28.133
I just wanted to tell you
that I'm sorry.

1:12:30.433 --> 1:12:31.400
I know I messed up.

1:12:31.433 --> 1:12:33.600
I know--

1:12:34.533 --> 1:12:39.267
I know I wasn't
a good father.

1:12:44.233 --> 1:12:47.133
I'm not gonna ask
for your forgiveness.

1:12:47.167 --> 1:12:48.200
I know I don't deserve it.

1:12:48.233 --> 1:12:50.567
I just--

1:12:56.300 --> 1:12:59.667
I'm not gonna leave you
again, Luke, ever.

1:13:01.600 --> 1:13:06.100
I'm gonna be here
for you, Son, okay?

1:13:15.167 --> 1:13:18.300
Maybe sometime,
whenever you're ready,

1:13:18.333 --> 1:13:21.033
we can--

1:13:21.533 --> 1:13:24.167
we can just
sit and talk.

1:13:33.667 --> 1:13:35.667
I love you, Son.

1:13:38.700 --> 1:13:48.733
[music]

1:13:48.733 --> 1:13:53.700
[music]

1:13:53.800 --> 1:14:08.200
[music]

1:14:08.300 --> 1:14:09.533
Rick: Hey.

1:14:09.567 --> 1:14:11.133
Anne: So?

1:14:11.167 --> 1:14:12.467
Rick: Yeah.

1:14:12.500 --> 1:14:14.533
Anne: Oh, good.

1:14:15.600 --> 1:14:18.100
Rick: We gotta get you home.

1:14:18.133 --> 1:14:19.467
Can I borrow the car, Mom?

1:14:19.500 --> 1:14:21.733
Anne: Well, of course.
Let me just find the keys.

1:14:25.300 --> 1:14:26.567
Rick: Thank you.

1:14:26.600 --> 1:14:27.700
Grace: For what?

1:14:27.733 --> 1:14:29.500
Rick: You know what for.

1:14:29.533 --> 1:14:34.467
For just being you,
and you know,

1:14:34.500 --> 1:14:37.133
just for everything.

1:14:37.167 --> 1:14:39.267
Grace: Of course.

1:14:39.633 --> 1:14:40.767
Anne: Here they are.
Rick: Thank you.

1:14:40.800 --> 1:14:42.167
Anne: And your coat.

1:14:42.200 --> 1:14:43.733
Rick: Okay.
Anne: All right.

1:14:43.767 --> 1:14:45.700
Well, Grace, I do not know
where you came from,

1:14:45.733 --> 1:14:47.333
but do not be a stranger,

1:14:47.367 --> 1:14:50.133
'cause you are welcome here
any time.

1:14:50.167 --> 1:14:52.467
Grace: Thank you.

1:14:54.433 --> 1:14:55.567
Rick: I'll be back soon,
okay, Mom?

1:14:55.600 --> 1:14:56.700
Anne: All right.
Rick: All right.

1:14:56.733 --> 1:14:58.100
Anne: Love you.
Rick: Love you.

1:14:58.133 --> 1:14:59.267
Grace: Good bye.

1:14:59.300 --> 1:15:00.467
Anne: Bye-bye.

1:15:00.500 --> 1:15:02.500
Drive safely now.

1:15:05.800 --> 1:15:16.033
[music]

1:15:16.033 --> 1:15:21.000
[music]

1:15:21.100 --> 1:15:31.133
[music]

1:15:31.133 --> 1:15:36.000
[music]

1:15:36.100 --> 1:15:42.167
[music]

1:15:42.267 --> 1:15:44.400
Grace: Just take
a left right up here.

1:15:44.433 --> 1:15:46.333
Rick: A left?

1:15:50.500 --> 1:15:52.233
What are we doing here?

1:15:52.267 --> 1:15:54.333
I thought you said that we're
gonna go see your family today.

1:15:54.367 --> 1:15:56.100
Grace: We are.

1:16:31.600 --> 1:16:34.033
Grace: Come, I want you
to meet my family.

1:16:34.067 --> 1:16:36.367
Rick: Okay.

1:16:45.733 --> 1:16:48.367
I don't know what to say, Grace.

1:16:51.133 --> 1:16:55.000
Grace: My husband
never made it back from war.

1:16:57.400 --> 1:17:01.733
He was killed not long
after Tommy drowned.

1:17:04.667 --> 1:17:06.700
Rick: I'm so sorry.

1:17:07.467 --> 1:17:10.267
Grace: I miss my babies.

1:17:12.467 --> 1:17:15.100
Happy Thanksgiving, Tom.

1:17:17.467 --> 1:17:20.100
This is Rick.

1:17:22.400 --> 1:17:26.500
If it wasn't for him, I probably
wouldn't be here today.

1:17:34.433 --> 1:17:37.433
Rick: Grace, the date
that your husband died,

1:17:38.133 --> 1:17:39.500
that's the day--

1:17:39.533 --> 1:17:42.400
Grace: Yeah,
5 years ago today.

1:17:44.533 --> 1:17:47.400
Rick: That's a sign,
isn't it?

1:17:50.500 --> 1:17:53.567
Everything that happened today
was supposed to happen.

1:17:53.600 --> 1:17:56.500
Right, Grace?

1:17:56.533 --> 1:18:00.367
Just like you said,
nothing happens by accident.

1:18:06.700 --> 1:18:09.733
That's God, right?

1:18:10.500 --> 1:18:13.400
Grace: I told you you had
to work on your lack of faith.

1:18:14.733 --> 1:18:17.767
Rick: You were right.

1:18:24.133 --> 1:18:26.533
You were right, Grace.

1:18:28.700 --> 1:18:31.233
Grace: My gosh.

1:18:31.267 --> 1:18:34.233
I can feel your heart
beating through your jacket.

1:18:34.267 --> 1:18:38.267
Rick: That's for you, Grace.

1:18:38.300 --> 1:18:41.067
That's for you.

1:18:45.300 --> 1:18:55.300
[music]

1:18:55.400 --> 1:19:04.067
[music]

1:19:06.067 --> 1:19:08.467
Rick: Hey, babe.

1:19:08.500 --> 1:19:11.433
I miss you.

1:19:13.300 --> 1:19:16.133
I met someone.

1:19:16.167 --> 1:19:19.133
Her name is Grace.

1:19:19.167 --> 1:19:21.267
We're just taking it day by day,

1:19:21.300 --> 1:19:25.267
but I got a good feeling
about it.

1:19:26.500 --> 1:19:29.800
I'm telling you this
because I can't help

1:19:29.833 --> 1:19:34.500
but think you were watching out
for me this whole time,

1:19:34.533 --> 1:19:37.667
and maybe this was
all your doing.

1:19:37.700 --> 1:19:40.233
Luke: Hey, Dad, come on!

1:19:41.633 --> 1:19:44.767
Rick: Anyway, I gotta go.

1:19:44.800 --> 1:19:48.267
I'm playing catch with our son.

1:19:50.400 --> 1:19:54.567
We'll talk again soon,
I promise.

1:19:57.833 --> 1:20:00.567
I love you.

1:20:02.067 --> 1:20:12.100
[music]

1:20:12.100 --> 1:20:17.067
[music]

1:20:17.167 --> 1:20:27.200
[music]

1:20:27.200 --> 1:20:32.067
[music]

1:20:32.167 --> 1:20:42.200
[music]

1:20:42.200 --> 1:20:47.067
[music]

1:20:47.167 --> 1:20:57.067
[music]

